byline.original: By WAI MOE and RICHARD C. PADDOCK
byline.contributor: Wai Moe reported from Naypyidaw, and Richard C. Paddock from Jakarta, Indonesia. Saw Nang contributed reporting from Mandalay, Myanmar.

lead_paragraph: Efforts by Myanmar’s democracy leader to negotiate her way to the top post this year have failed, associates of hers confirmed on Monday.

headline.print_headline: Myanmar’s Democracy Leader Finds Path to Presidency Blocked by Military
headline.main: Aung San Suu Kyi Finds Roadblocks on Path to Presidency

snippet: Efforts by Myanmar’s democracy leader to negotiate her way to the top post this year have failed, associates of hers confirmed on Monday.
abstract: Myanmar's National League for Democracy party, which is set to take over Parliament, confirms that efforts to elect Daw Aung San Suu Kyi as president have failed; party's leader is barred under Constitutional clause due to foreign citizenship of her sons; further details on transfer of power and leadership remain unclear.
